<h2 id=3D"idea">1. Idea</h2>

<p>A <em>Boolean algebra</em> or <em>Boolean <a class=3D"existingWikiWord" =
href=3D"https://ncatlab.org/nlab/show/lattice">lattice</a></em> is an algeb=
raic structure which models classical <a class=3D"existingWikiWord" href=3D=
"https://ncatlab.org/nlab/show/propositional+calculus">propositional calcul=
us</a>, roughly the fragment of the logical calculus which deals with the b=
asic logical connectives =E2=80=9Cand=E2=80=9D, =E2=80=9Cor=E2=80=9D, =E2=
=80=9Cimplies=E2=80=9D, and =E2=80=9Cnot=E2=80=9D.</p>

<h2 id=3D"definitions">2. Definitions</h2>

<h3 id=3D"general">General</h3>

<p>There are many known ways of defining a <strong>Boolean algebra</strong>=
 or <strong>Boolean lattice</strong>. Here are just a few:</p>

<ul>
<li>
<p>A Boolean algebra is a <a class=3D"existingWikiWord" href=3D"https://nca=
tlab.org/nlab/show/complement">complemented</a> <a class=3D"existingWikiWor=
d" href=3D"https://ncatlab.org/nlab/show/distributive+lattice">distributive=
 lattice</a>.</p>
</li>

<li>
<p>A Boolean algebra is a <a class=3D"existingWikiWord" href=3D"https://nca=
tlab.org/nlab/show/Heyting+algebra">Heyting algebra</a> <math xmlns=3D"http=
://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML" display=3D"inline" class=3D"maruku-mathml">=
<semantics><mrow><mi>H</mi></mrow><annotation encoding=3D"application/x-tex=
">H</annotation></semantics></math> satisfying the <a class=3D"existingWiki=
Word" href=3D"https://ncatlab.org/nlab/show/law+of+excluded+middle">law of =
excluded middle</a>, which means</p>
<div class=3D"maruku-equation"><math xmlns=3D"http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/M=
athML" display=3D"block" class=3D"maruku-mathml" style=3D"min-width: 179px;=
"><semantics><mrow><msub><mo>=E2=88=80</mo> <mrow><mi>x</mi><mo>=E2=88=88</=
mo><mi>H</mi></mrow></msub><mi>x</mi><mo>=E2=88=A8</mo><mo>=C2=AC</mo><mi>x=
</mi><mo>=3D</mo><mo>=E2=8A=A4</mo></mrow><annotation encoding=3D"applicati=
on/x-tex">\forall_{x \in H} x \vee \neg x =3D \top</annotation></semantics>=
</math></div>
<p>or (equivalently) satisfying the <a class=3D"existingWikiWord" href=3D"h=
ttps://ncatlab.org/nlab/show/double+negation+law">double negation law</a>, =
which means</p>
<div class=3D"maruku-equation"><math xmlns=3D"http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/M=
athML" display=3D"block" class=3D"maruku-mathml" style=3D"min-width: 154px;=
"><semantics><mrow><mo>=C2=AC</mo><mo>=C2=AC</mo><mo>=3D</mo><mi>id</mi><mo=
>:</mo><mi>H</mi><mo>=E2=86=92</mo><mi>H</mi></mrow><annotation encoding=3D=
"application/x-tex">\neg \neg =3D id: H \to H</annotation></semantics></mat=
h></div></li>

<li>
<p>A Boolean algebra is a <a class=3D"existingWikiWord" href=3D"https://nca=
tlab.org/nlab/show/lattice">lattice</a> <math xmlns=3D"http://www.w3.org/19=
98/Math/MathML" display=3D"inline" class=3D"maruku-mathml"><semantics><mrow=
><mi>L</mi></mrow><annotation encoding=3D"application/x-tex">L</annotation>=
</semantics></math> equipped with a function <math xmlns=3D"http://www.w3.o=
rg/1998/Math/MathML" display=3D"inline" class=3D"maruku-mathml"><semantics>=
<mrow><mo>=C2=AC</mo><mo>:</mo><mi>L</mi><mo>=E2=86=92</mo><mi>L</mi></mrow=
><annotation encoding=3D"application/x-tex">\neg: L \to L</annotation></sem=
antics></math> satisfying</p>
<div class=3D"maruku-equation"><math xmlns=3D"http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/M=
athML" display=3D"block" class=3D"maruku-mathml" style=3D"min-width: 285px;=
"><semantics><mrow><mi>a</mi><mo>=E2=88=A7</mo><mi>b</mi><mo>=E2=89=A4</mo>=
<mi>c</mi><mspace width=3D"2em"/><mi>iff</mi><mspace width=3D"2em"/><mi>a</=
mi><mo>=E2=89=A4</mo><mo>=C2=AC</mo><mi>b</mi><mo>=E2=88=A8</mo><mi>c</mi><=
/mrow><annotation encoding=3D"application/x-tex">a \wedge b \leq c \qquad i=
ff \qquad a \leq \neg b \vee c</annotation></semantics></math></div></li>

<li>
<p>A Boolean algebra is a cartesian <a class=3D"existingWikiWord" href=3D"h=
ttps://ncatlab.org/nlab/show/star-autonomous+category">*-autonomous poset</=
a> i.e. a <a class=3D"existingWikiWord" href=3D"https://ncatlab.org/nlab/sh=
ow/meet-semilattice">meet-semilattice</a> which is a <math xmlns=3D"http://=
www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML" display=3D"inline" class=3D"maruku-mathml"><se=
mantics><mrow><mo>*</mo></mrow><annotation encoding=3D"application/x-tex">*=
</annotation></semantics></math>-autonomous category with tensor product <m=
ath xmlns=3D"http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML" display=3D"inline" class=
=3D"maruku-mathml"><semantics><mrow><mi>a</mi><mo>=E2=88=A7</mo><mi>b</mi><=
/mrow><annotation encoding=3D"application/x-tex">a \wedge b</annotation></s=
emantics></math> and monoidal unit <math xmlns=3D"http://www.w3.org/1998/Ma=
th/MathML" display=3D"inline" class=3D"maruku-mathml"><semantics><mrow><mo>=
=E2=8A=A4</mo></mrow><annotation encoding=3D"application/x-tex">\top</annot=
ation></semantics></math>. In other words, a Boolean algebra is a cartesian=
 closed poset <math xmlns=3D"http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML" display=3D=
"inline" class=3D"maruku-mathml"><semantics><mrow><mi>P</mi></mrow><annotat=
ion encoding=3D"application/x-tex">P</annotation></semantics></math> togeth=
er with an object <math xmlns=3D"http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML" displa=
y=3D"inline" class=3D"maruku-mathml"><semantics><mrow><mo>=E2=8A=A5</mo></m=
row><annotation encoding=3D"application/x-tex">\bot</annotation></semantics=
></math> such that <math xmlns=3D"http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML" displ=
ay=3D"inline" class=3D"maruku-mathml"><semantics><mrow><mo stretchy=3D"fals=
e">(</mo><mi>a</mi><mo>=E2=86=92</mo><mo>=E2=8A=A5</mo><mo stretchy=3D"fals=
e">)</mo><mo>=E2=86=92</mo><mo>=E2=8A=A5</mo><mo>=E2=89=A4</mo><mi>a</mi></=
mrow><annotation encoding=3D"application/x-tex">(a \rightarrow \bot) \right=
arrow \bot \le a</annotation></semantics></math> for every <math xmlns=3D"h=
ttp://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML" display=3D"inline" class=3D"maruku-mathm=
l"><semantics><mrow><mi>a</mi><mo>=E2=88=88</mo><mi>P</mi></mrow><annotatio=
n encoding=3D"application/x-tex">a \in P</annotation></semantics></math>.</=
p>
</li>
</ul>

<h3 id=3D"explicitly">Explicitly</h3>

<p>There are even two explicit definitions: <a class=3D"existingWikiWord" h=
ref=3D"https://ncatlab.org/nlab/show/order+theory">order-theoretic</a> and =
algebraic.</p>

<p>A <strong>Boolean lattice</strong> is a <a class=3D"existingWikiWord" hr=
ef=3D"https://ncatlab.org/nlab/show/poset">poset</a> such that:</p>

<ul>
<li>there is an element <math xmlns=3D"http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML" =
display=3D"inline" class=3D"maruku-mathml"><semantics><mrow><mo>=E2=8A=A4</=
mo></mrow><annotation encoding=3D"application/x-tex">\top</annotation></sem=
antics></math> (a <a class=3D"existingWikiWord" href=3D"https://ncatlab.org=
/nlab/show/top+element">top element</a>) such that <math xmlns=3D"http://ww=
w.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML" display=3D"inline" class=3D"maruku-mathml"><sema=
ntics><mrow><mi>x</mi><mo>=E2=89=A4</mo><mo>=E2=8A=A4</mo></mrow><annotatio=
n encoding=3D"application/x-tex">x \leq \top</annotation></semantics></math=
> always holds;</li>

<li>there is an element <math xmlns=3D"http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML" =
display=3D"inline" class=3D"maruku-mathml"><semantics><mrow><mo>=E2=8A=A5</=
mo></mrow><annotation encoding=3D"application/x-tex">\bot</annotation></sem=
antics></math> (a <a class=3D"existingWikiWord" href=3D"https://ncatlab.org=
/nlab/show/bottom+element">bottom element</a>) such that <math xmlns=3D"htt=
p://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML" display=3D"inline" class=3D"maruku-mathml"=
><semantics><mrow><mo>=E2=8A=A5</mo><mo>=E2=89=A4</mo><mi>x</mi></mrow><ann=
otation encoding=3D"application/x-tex">\bot \leq x</annotation></semantics>=
</math> always holds;</li>

<li>given elements <math xmlns=3D"http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML" displ=
ay=3D"inline" class=3D"maruku-mathml"><semantics><mrow><mi>a</mi></mrow><an=
notation encoding=3D"application/x-tex">a</annotation></semantics></math> a=
nd <math xmlns=3D"http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML" display=3D"inline" cl=
ass=3D"maruku-mathml"><semantics><mrow><mi>b</mi></mrow><annotation encodin=
g=3D"application/x-tex">b</annotation></semantics></math>, there is an elem=
ent <math xmlns=3D"http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML" display=3D"inline" c=
lass=3D"maruku-mathml"><semantics><mrow><mi>a</mi><mo>=E2=88=A7</mo><mi>b</=
mi></mrow><annotation encoding=3D"application/x-tex">a \wedge b</annotation=
></semantics></math> (a <a class=3D"existingWikiWord" href=3D"https://ncatl=
ab.org/nlab/show/meet">meet</a> of <math xmlns=3D"http://www.w3.org/1998/Ma=
th/MathML" display=3D"inline" class=3D"maruku-mathml"><semantics><mrow><mi>=
a</mi></mrow><annotation encoding=3D"application/x-tex">a</annotation></sem=
antics></math> and <math xmlns=3D"http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML" displ=
ay=3D"inline" class=3D"maruku-mathml"><semantics><mrow><mi>b</mi></mrow><an=
notation encoding=3D"application/x-tex">b</annotation></semantics></math>) =
such that <math xmlns=3D"http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML" display=3D"inl=
ine" class=3D"maruku-mathml"><semantics><mrow><mi>x</mi><mo>=E2=89=A4</mo><=
mi>a</mi><mo>=E2=88=A7</mo><mi>b</mi></mrow><annotation encoding=3D"applica=
tion/x-tex">x \leq a \wedge b</annotation></semantics></math> holds iff <ma=
th xmlns=3D"http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML" display=3D"inline" class=3D=
"maruku-mathml"><semantics><mrow><mi>x</mi><mo>=E2=89=A4</mo><mi>a</mi></mr=
ow><annotation encoding=3D"application/x-tex">x \leq a</annotation></semant=
ics></math> and <math xmlns=3D"http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML" display=
=3D"inline" class=3D"maruku-mathml"><semantics><mrow><mi>x</mi><mo>=E2=89=
=A4</mo><mi>b</mi></mrow><annotation encoding=3D"application/x-tex">x \leq =
b</annotation></semantics></math>;</li>

<li>given elements <math xmlns=3D"http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML" displ=
ay=3D"inline" class=3D"maruku-mathml"><semantics><mrow><mi>a</mi></mrow><an=
notation encoding=3D"application/x-tex">a</annotation></semantics></math> a=
nd <math xmlns=3D"http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML" display=3D"inline" cl=
ass=3D"maruku-mathml"><semantics><mrow><mi>b</mi></mrow><annotation encodin=
g=3D"application/x-tex">b</annotation></semantics></math>, there is an elem=
ent <math xmlns=3D"http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML" display=3D"inline" c=
lass=3D"maruku-mathml"><semantics><mrow><mi>a</mi><mo>=E2=88=A8</mo><mi>b</=
mi></mrow><annotation encoding=3D"application/x-tex">a \vee b</annotation><=
/semantics></math> (a <a class=3D"existingWikiWord" href=3D"https://ncatlab=
.org/nlab/show/join">join</a> of <math xmlns=3D"http://www.w3.org/1998/Math=
/MathML" display=3D"inline" class=3D"maruku-mathml"><semantics><mrow><mi>a<=
/mi></mrow><annotation encoding=3D"application/x-tex">a</annotation></seman=
tics></math> and <math xmlns=3D"http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML" display=
=3D"inline" class=3D"maruku-mathml"><semantics><mrow><mi>b</mi></mrow><anno=
tation encoding=3D"application/x-tex">b</annotation></semantics></math>) su=
ch that <math xmlns=3D"http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML" display=3D"inlin=
e" class=3D"maruku-mathml"><semantics><mrow><mi>a</mi><mo>=E2=88=A8</mo><mi=
>b</mi><mo>=E2=89=A4</mo><mi>x</mi></mrow><annotation encoding=3D"applicati=
on/x-tex">a \vee b \leq x</annotation></semantics></math> holds iff <math x=
mlns=3D"http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML" display=3D"inline" class=3D"mar=
uku-mathml"><semantics><mrow><mi>a</mi><mo>=E2=89=A4</mo><mi>x</mi></mrow><=
annotation encoding=3D"application/x-tex">a \leq x</annotation></semantics>=
</math> and <math xmlns=3D"http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML" display=3D"i=
nline" class=3D"maruku-mathml"><semantics><mrow><mi>b</mi><mo>=E2=89=A4</mo=
><mi>x</mi></mrow><annotation encoding=3D"application/x-tex">b \leq x</anno=
tation></semantics></math>;</li>

<li>given an element <math xmlns=3D"http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML" dis=
play=3D"inline" class=3D"maruku-mathml"><semantics><mrow><mi>a</mi></mrow><=
annotation encoding=3D"application/x-tex">a</annotation></semantics></math>=
, there is an element <math xmlns=3D"http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML" di=
splay=3D"inline" class=3D"maruku-mathml"><semantics><mrow><mo>=C2=AC</mo><m=
i>a</mi></mrow><annotation encoding=3D"application/x-tex">\neg{a}</annotati=
on></semantics></math> (a <a class=3D"existingWikiWord" href=3D"https://nca=
tlab.org/nlab/show/complement">complement</a> of <math xmlns=3D"http://www.=
w3.org/1998/Math/MathML" display=3D"inline" class=3D"maruku-mathml"><semant=
ics><mrow><mi>a</mi></mrow><annotation encoding=3D"application/x-tex">a</an=
notation></semantics></math>) such that <math xmlns=3D"http://www.w3.org/19=
98/Math/MathML" display=3D"inline" class=3D"maruku-mathml"><semantics><mrow=
><mi>a</mi><mo>=E2=88=A7</mo><mo>=C2=AC</mo><mi>a</mi><mo>=E2=89=A4</mo><mo=
>=E2=8A=A5</mo></mrow><annotation encoding=3D"application/x-tex">a \wedge \=
neg{a} \leq \bot</annotation></semantics></math> and <math xmlns=3D"http://=
www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML" display=3D"inline" class=3D"maruku-mathml"><se=
mantics><mrow><mo>=E2=8A=A4</mo><mo>=E2=89=A4</mo><mi>a</mi><mo>=E2=88=A8</=
mo><mo>=C2=AC</mo><mi>a</mi></mrow><annotation encoding=3D"application/x-te=
x">\top \leq a \vee \neg{a}</annotation></semantics></math>;</li>

<li>given elements <math xmlns=3D"http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML" displ=
ay=3D"inline" class=3D"maruku-mathml"><semantics><mrow><mi>a</mi></mrow><an=
notation encoding=3D"application/x-tex">a</annotation></semantics></math>, =
<math xmlns=3D"http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML" display=3D"inline" class=
=3D"maruku-mathml"><semantics><mrow><mi>b</mi></mrow><annotation encoding=
=3D"application/x-tex">b</annotation></semantics></math>, and <math xmlns=
=3D"http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML" display=3D"inline" class=3D"maruku-=
mathml"><semantics><mrow><mi>c</mi></mrow><annotation encoding=3D"applicati=
on/x-tex">c</annotation></semantics></math>, we have <math xmlns=3D"http://=
www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML" display=3D"inline" class=3D"maruku-mathml"><se=
mantics><mrow><mi>a</mi><mo>=E2=88=A7</mo><mo stretchy=3D"false">(</mo><mi>=
b</mi><mo>=E2=88=A8</mo><mi>c</mi><mo stretchy=3D"false">)</mo><mo>=E2=89=
=A4</mo><mo stretchy=3D"false">(</mo><mi>a</mi><mo>=E2=88=A7</mo><mi>b</mi>=
<mo stretchy=3D"false">)</mo><mo>=E2=88=A8</mo><mo stretchy=3D"false">(</mo=
><mi>a</mi><mo>=E2=88=A7</mo><mi>c</mi><mo stretchy=3D"false">)</mo></mrow>=
<annotation encoding=3D"application/x-tex">a \wedge (b \vee c) \leq (a \wed=
ge b) \vee (a \wedge c)</annotation></semantics></math>.</li>
